&lt;h2 id=&#34;dec-25----dec-29-heiland&#34;&gt;Dec 25 &amp;ndash; Dec 29 (Heiland)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lectures and talks (2 Lecture Units)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;note-china-doesnt-celebrate-christmas-and-jh-is-in-china-anyways&#34;&gt;&amp;laquo;&amp;laquo;&amp;laquo;&amp;lt; HEAD
Note: &lt;em&gt;China doesn&amp;rsquo;t celebrate christmas and JH is in China anyways&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;lecture-details&#34;&gt;Lecture Details&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each lecture consists of three units of 45 minutes each. There might be exercise sheets to be solved by the students between the lectures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l1-by-zuazua&#34;&gt;L1 (by Zuazua)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L1A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L1B&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L1C&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l2-by-heilandgosea&#34;&gt;L2 (by Heiland/Gosea)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L2A&lt;/strong&gt;: Linear time-invariant (LTI) systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L2B&lt;/strong&gt;: Realizations and control theory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L2C&lt;/strong&gt;: Frequency domain representation of LTI systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l3-edmd-and-control-by-worthmann-schaller-philipp&#34;&gt;L3 (e)DMD and Control (by Worthmann, Schaller, Philipp)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L3A&lt;/strong&gt;: introduction, algorithm, data-driven surrogate models, error bounds for (stochastic) nonlinear dynamical systems, i.e., with i.i.d. and ergodic sampling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L3B&lt;/strong&gt;: eDMD with control and control using the control-affine structure, predictive control in the Koopman framework with guarantees: Model Predictive Control (MPC), practical asymptotic stability, state- and control-depedent error bounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L3C&lt;/strong&gt;: kernel-based eDMD: RKHS, reproducing property, estimation error, invariance of the RKHS, OU process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l4-nonlinear-port-hamiltonian-systems-and-control-by-worthmann-schaller-philipp&#34;&gt;L4 Nonlinear Port-Hamiltonian Systems and Control (by Worthmann, Schaller, Philipp)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L4A&lt;/strong&gt;: introductory lecture: Why pH systems? State-space and geometic modelling, coupling via (Dirac-) structures, energy- and entropy balances, dissipativity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L4B&lt;/strong&gt;: (optimal) control: passivity-based control, minimal energy control, optimality system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L4C&lt;/strong&gt;: Adaptive building control, outlook to the infinite-dimensional case (system nodes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l5-system-identification-si-and-reduced-order-modeling-rom-by-gosea&#34;&gt;L5 System Identification (SI) and Reduced-order Modeling (RoM) (by Gosea)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L5A&lt;/strong&gt;: Introductory Lecture: why is complexity reduction important? Identification vs reduction of dynamical systems - an overview.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L5B&lt;/strong&gt; Methods in the time domain: SI + RoM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L5C&lt;/strong&gt; Methods in the frequency domain: SI + RoM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l6-data-driven-system-descriptions-in-predictive-control-by-schmitz--faulwasser&#34;&gt;L6 Data-driven System Descriptions in Predictive Control (by Schmitz &amp;amp; Faulwasser)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L6A&lt;/strong&gt;: The fundamental lemma and determinsitic data-driven MPC (by Schmitz)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L6B&lt;/strong&gt;: The stochastic extension to the fundamental lemma (by Faulwasser)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L6C&lt;/strong&gt;: Stochastic data-driven MPC (by Faulwasser)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l8-linear-systems-theory-and-mor-by-heiland&#34;&gt;L8 Linear Systems Theory and MOR (by Heiland)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L8A&lt;/strong&gt;: Linear time-invariant Systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L8B&lt;/strong&gt;: Balanced Realizations and Truncations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L8C&lt;/strong&gt;: LQG Balanced Truncation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l9-riccati-equations-and-robust-control-by-heiland&#34;&gt;L9 Riccati Equations and Robust Control (by Heiland)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L9A&lt;/strong&gt;: Linear-Quadratic Regulator and Riccati&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L9B&lt;/strong&gt;: $H_\infty$-robust Control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L9C&lt;/strong&gt;: Numerical Solution of Large-scale $H_\infty$ Riccati Equations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;l10-nonlinear-control-with-almost-linear-theory-by-heiland&#34;&gt;L10 Nonlinear Control with Almost Linear Theory (by Heiland)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L10A&lt;/strong&gt;: State-dependent Riccati Equations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L10B&lt;/strong&gt;: Linear Parameter-varying Systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L10C&lt;/strong&gt;: Applications in Flow Control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
